{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"df47a0a7-f51c-478e-a3ef-1f8b4aef62de","content":"MSTest v3 dropped support for `.testsettings` files. Here's what I did:\n\n1. **Created `local.runsettings`** — the modern replacement. It maps your old settings:\n   - `TestTimeout` → `<MSTest><TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>`\n   - `AssemblyResolution` with `useLoadContext` → `<DeploymentEnabled>false</DeploymentEnabled>` (disables the deployment directory, loading from the test directory directly)\n\n2. **Updated `TestProject.csproj`** — added `<RunSettingsFilePath>` so `dotnet test` picks it up automatically.\n\nYou can now safely delete `local.testsettings`. Run `dotnet test` — it will use the new `.runsettings` file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a8f92b60-6895-49db-aa04-2f3607f9d74d","outputTokens":188},"id":"ecdc7baa-d1a1-4c14-b844-dd69e5431c6d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:13:23.958Z","parentId":"cee62d6d-7870-4104-b3fe-fca6a1ebf503"}
